m></text:list><text:p text:style-name="P11">Edit Claim Rules</text:p><text:list xml:id="list3913819808" text:style-name="WWNum6"><text:list-item><text:p text:style-name="P4">In the AD FS MMC, expand the Trust Relationships and click on Relying Parties Trusts.</text:p></text:list-item><text:list-item><text:p text:style-name="P4">Right-click the new Relying Party that was just created, and select <text:span text:style-name="T2">Edit Claim Rulesâ¦</text:span><text:span text:style-name="T3"><text:line-break/><text:line-break/><text:line-break/><text:line-break/></text:span><draw:frame draw:style-name="fr1" draw:name="image10.png" text:anchor-type="as-char" svg:width="6.5102in" svg:height="4.9583in" draw:z-index="0"><draw:image xlink:href="Pictures/1000020100000271000001DCD3E7DE9A2F970D27.png" xlink:type="simple" xlink:show="embed" xlink:actuate="onLoad" loext:mime-type="image/png"/></draw:frame><text:span text:style-name="T3"><text:line-break/><text:line-break/><text:line-break/></text:span></text:p></text:list-item><text:list-item><text:p text:style-name="P4">Click <text:span text:style-name="T2">Add Ruleâ¦</text:span></text:p></text:list-item><text:list-item><text:p text:style-name="P4">Select <text:span text:style-name="T2">Send LDAP Attributes as Claims</text:span> from the dropdown list.</text:p></text:list-item><text:list-item><text:p text:style-name="P4">Click <text:span text:style-name="T2">Next</text:span>.<text:span text:style-name="T3"><text:line-break/><text:line-break/><text:line-break/><text:line-break/></text:span><draw:frame draw:style-name="fr1" draw:name="image16.png" text:anchor-type="as-char" svg:width="6.5in" svg:height="3.7189in" draw:z-index="0"><draw:image xlink:href="Pictures/100002010000027000000165E43D6EA5924FCF90.png" xlink:type="simple" xlink:show="embed" xlink:actuate="onLoad" loext:mime-type="image/png"/></draw:frame><text:span text:style-name="T3"><text:line-break/><text:line-break/><text:line-break/></text:span></text:p></text:list-ite