ield. The default URL is:Â <text:span text:style-name="T1">https://[SERVER_FQDN]/adfs/ls/?wa=wsignout1.0</text:span></text:p></text:list-item><text:list-item><text:p text:style-name="P5">Click <text:span text:style-name="T2">OK</text:span> to close the Add an Endpoint window.<text:span text:style-name="T3"><text:line-break/><text:line-break/><text:line-break/><text:line-break/></text:span><draw:frame draw:style-name="fr1" draw:name="image7.png" text:anchor-type="as-char" svg:width="6.4689in" svg:height="5.7811in" draw:z-index="0"><draw:image xlink:href="Pictures/100002010000026D0000022BD87FB9C1FEDA5151.png" xlink:type="simple" xlink:show="embed" xlink:actuate="onLoad" loext:mime-type="image/png"/></draw:frame></text:p></text:list-item></text:list><text:p text:style-name="P9"/><text:p text:style-name="P10">Configure AD Access Groups (Optional)</text:p><text:list xml:id="list2258443827" text:style-name="WWNum2"><text:list-item><text:p text:style-name="P6">In the AD FS MMC, expand the Trust Relationships and click on Relying Parties Trusts.</text:p></text:list-item><text:list-item><text:p text:style-name="P6">Right-click the new Relying Party just created, and select <text:span text:style-name="T2">Edit Claim Rulesâ¦</text:span></text:p></text:list-item><text:list-item><text:p text:style-name="P6">Click the <text:span text:style-name="T2">Issuance Authorization Rule</text:span> tab.</text:p></text:list-item><text:list-item><text:p text:style-name="P6"><text:soft-page-break/>Click <text:span text:style-name="T2">Add Ruleâ¦</text:span><text:span text:style-name="T3"><text:line-break/><text:line-break/><text:line-break/><text:line-break/></text:span><draw:frame draw:style-name="fr1" draw:name="image2.png" text:anchor-type="as-char" svg:width="6.0626in" svg:height="5.198in" draw:z-index="0"><draw:image xlink:href="Pictures/1000020100000246000001F3DC78A7AF1087D34D.png" xlink:type="simple" xlink:show="embed" xlink:actuate="onLoad" loext:mime-type="image/png"/></draw:frame><text:span text:style-name="T3"><text:line-break/><text:line-break/><text:line-break/></text:span></text:p></text:list-item><text:list-item><text:p text:style-name="P6">Select <text:span text:style-name="T2">Permit or Deny Users Based on Incoming Claim</text:span> from the dropdown list.<text:span text:style-name="T3"><text:line-break/><text:line-break/><text:line-break/><text:line-break/></text:span><draw:frame draw:style-name="fr1" draw:name="image5.png" text:anchor-type="as-char" svg:width="5.3854in" svg:height="4.3335in" draw:z-index="0"><draw:image xlink:href="Pictures/1000020100000205000001A0B380E2CB31D19C9E.png" xlink:type="simple" xlink:show="embed" xlink:actuate="onLoad" loext:mime-type="image/png"/></draw:frame><text:span text:style-name="T3"><text:line-break/><text:line-break/><text:line-break/></text:span></text:p></text:list-item><text:list-item><text:p text:style-name="P6">Enter a claim rule name.</text:p></text:list-item><text:list-item><text:p text:style-name="P6">Select the appropriate criteria from the <text:span text:style-name="T2">Incoming claim type</text:span> drop down list. In this example, we are basing it on AD group.<text:span text:style-name="T3"><text:line-break/><text:line-break/><text:line-break/><text:line-break/></text:span><draw:frame draw:style-name="fr1" draw:name="image18.png" text:anchor-type="as-char" svg:width="6.5in" svg:height="5.2917in" draw:z-index="0"><draw:image xlink:href="Pictures/1000020100000270000001FC44DF349B5FB41F62.png" xlink:type="simple" xlink:show="embed" xlink:actuate="onLoad" loext:mime-type="image/png"/></draw:frame></text:p></text:list-item></text:list><text:p text:style-name="P11">Restart the ADFS Service</text:p><text:list xml:id="list2815379720" text:style-name="WWNum3"><text:list-item><text:p text:style-name="P7">On your ADFS server, open the Server Manager.</text:p></text:list-item><text:list-item><text:p text:style-name="P7">Click <text:span text:style-name="T2">Tools</text:span>, and select <text:span text:style-name="T2">Services</text:span>.<text:span text:style-name="T3"><text:line-break/><text:line-break/><text:line-break/><text:line-break/></text:span><draw:frame draw:style-name="fr1" draw:name="image14.png" text:anchor-type="as-char" svg:width="6.5in" svg:height="4.9898in" draw:z-index="0"><draw:image xlink:href="Pictures/1000020100000270000001DFF3F0E8C2AEED6587.png" xlink:type="simple" xlink:show="embed" xlink:actuate="onLoad" loext:mime-type="image/png"/></draw:frame><text:span text:style-name="T3"><text:line-break/><text:line-break/><text:line-break/></text:span></text:p></text:list-item><text:list-item><text:p text:style-name="P7">Right-click the <text:span text:style-name="T2">Active Directory Federation Services</text:span> service.</text:p></text:list-item><text:list-item><text:p text:style-name="P7">Click <text:span text:style-name="T2">Restart</text:span>.<text:span text:style-name="T3"><text:line-break/><text:line-break/><text:line-break/><text:line-break/></text:span><draw:frame draw:style-name="fr1" draw:name="image8.png" text:anchor-type="as-char" svg:width="6.5102in" svg:height="3.3543in" draw:z-index="0"><draw:image xlink:href="Pictures/100002010000027100000142AA69866E3997E6A7.png" xlink:type="simple" xlink:show="embed" xlink:actuate="onLoad" loext:mime-type="image/png"/></draw:frame></text:p></text:list-item></text:list><text:p text:style-name="P11">Customize ADFS User Sign-in Page (Optional)</text:p><text:p text:style-name="P8">Options for changing the way your user sign-in page looks and behaves can be found here:</text:p><text:p text:style-name="P8"><text:a xlink:type="simple" xlink:href="https://docs.microsoft.com/en-us/windows-server/identity/ad-fs/operations/ad-fs-user-sign-in-customization" text:style-name="ListLabel_20_55" text:visited-style-name="ListLabel_20_55"><text:span text:style-name="T5">https://docs.microsoft.com/en-us/windows-server/identity/ad-fs/operations/ad-fs-user-sign-in-customization</text:span></text:a></text:p>